{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0167ndrApEwaEyTDsMqMK2PN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FJ35ncUACESPEhwXzd6AXT","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/quinn/output/cloud_deployment_plan.md","content":"# Cloud Deployment Plan — Kalshi Trading Pipeline\n**Author**: Quinn (Cloud Engineer)\n**Task**: T267\n**Date**: 2026-04-03\n**Target**: AWS (primary) with GCP alternative noted\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n                          ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                          │              AWS VPC (us-east-1)         │\n                          │                                           │\n  Internet ───── ALB ──── │ ── EC2 t3.small ───────────────────────  │\n  (HTTPS:443)   (port 80) │   ┌───────────────────────────────────┐  │\n                          │   │  Docker Compose                   │  │\n                          │   │  ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐  │  │\n                          │   │  │  dashboard  │ │  trading-   │  │  │\n                          │   │  │  (port 3199)│ │  api(:8080) │  │  │\n                          │   │  └─────────────┘ └──────┬──────┘  │  │\n                          │   │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n                          │   │  │  scheduler (loop every 10m) │  │  │\n                          │   │  └─────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n                          │   └───────────────────────────────────┘  │\n                          │                    │                       │\n                          │   RDS PostgreSQL ──┘                      │\n                          │   (db.t3.micro, private subnet)           │\n                          └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                      │\n                               Secrets Manager\n                               (KALSHI_API_KEY, DB creds, JWT_SECRET)\n                                      │\n                               CloudWatch Logs\n                               (pipeline + dashboard logs)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Why This Architecture\n\n**Single EC2 + Docker Compose** rather than ECS/EKS:\n- One person can deploy in a day\n- No cluster management overhead\n- The existing `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` work as-is with minor additions\n- Easy SSH access for debugging during early production phase\n- Total cost: ~$42/month (vs $100+/month for ECS Fargate + ALB)\n\n**Upgrade path**: Once trading is proven in production, migrate `trading-api` and `scheduler` to ECS Fargate without changing application code.\n\n---\n\n## Step-by-Step Deployment\n\n### 1. Prerequisites (30 min)\n\n```bash\n# Install AWS CLI + Terraform\nbrew install awscli terraform\naws configure  # region: us-east-1\n```\n\n### 2. Terraform — VPC + EC2 + RDS + Secrets\n\nSave as `infrastructure/trading/main.tf`:\n\n```hcl\nterraform {\n  required_providers {\n    aws = { source = \"hashicorp/aws\", version = \"~> 5.0\" }\n  }\n  backend \"s3\" {\n    bucket = \"tokenfly-tf-state\"\n    key    = \"trading/terraform.tfstate\"\n    region = \"us-east-1\"\n  }\n}\n\nprovider \"aws\" { region = \"us-east-1\" }\n\n# ── VPC ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_vpc\" \"trading\" {\n  cidr_block           = \"10.0.0.0/16\"\n  enable_dns_hostnames = true\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_internet_gateway\" \"igw\" {\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\n}\n\nresource \"aws_subnet\" \"public_a\" {\n  vpc_id                  = aws_vpc.trading.id\n  cidr_block              = \"10.0.1.0/24\"\n  availability_zone       = \"us-east-1a\"\n  map_public_ip_on_launch = true\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-public-a\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_subnet\" \"private_a\" {\n  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.trading.id\n  cidr_block        = \"10.0.10.0/24\"\n  availability_zone = \"us-east-1a\"\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-private-a\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_subnet\" \"private_b\" {\n  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.trading.id\n  cidr_block        = \"10.0.11.0/24\"\n  availability_zone = \"us-east-1b\"\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-private-b\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_route_table\" \"public\" {\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\n  route {\n    cidr_block = \"0.0.0.0/0\"\n    gateway_id = aws_internet_gateway.igw.id\n  }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_route_table_association\" \"public_a\" {\n  subnet_id      = aws_subnet.public_a.id\n  route_table_id = aws_route_table.public.id\n}\n\n# ── Security Groups ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_security_group\" \"ec2\" {\n  name   = \"tokenfly-ec2\"\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\n\n  ingress {\n    description = \"Dashboard\"\n    from_port   = 3199\n    to_port     = 3199\n    protocol    = \"tcp\"\n    cidr_blocks = [var.allowed_cidr]   # Set to your IP: \"1.2.3.4/32\"\n  }\n  ingress {\n    description = \"SSH\"\n    from_port   = 22\n    to_port     = 22\n    protocol    = \"tcp\"\n    cidr_blocks = [var.allowed_cidr]\n  }\n  egress {\n    from_port   = 0\n    to_port     = 0\n    protocol    = \"-1\"\n    cidr_blocks = [\"0.0.0.0/0\"]\n  }\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-ec2-sg\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_security_group\" \"rds\" {\n  name   = \"tokenfly-rds\"\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\n\n  ingress {\n    description     = \"Postgres from EC2 only\"\n    from_port       = 5432\n    to_port         = 5432\n    protocol        = \"tcp\"\n    security_groups = [aws_security_group.ec2.id]\n  }\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-rds-sg\" }\n}\n\n# ── RDS PostgreSQL ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_db_subnet_group\" \"trading\" {\n  name       = \"tokenfly-trading\"\n  subnet_ids = [aws_subnet.private_a.id, aws_subnet.private_b.id]\n}\n\nresource \"random_password\" \"db\" {\n  length  = 32\n  special = false\n}\n\nresource \"aws_db_instance\" \"trading\" {\n  identifier        = \"tokenfly-trading\"\n  engine            = \"postgres\"\n  engine_version    = \"16.3\"\n  instance_class    = \"db.t3.micro\"\n  allocated_storage = 20\n  storage_type      = \"gp2\"\n\n  db_name  = \"kalshi_trading\"\n  username = \"trading_user\"\n  password = random_password.db.result\n\n  db_subnet_group_name   = aws_db_subnet_group.trading.name\n  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.rds.id]\n\n  backup_retention_period   = 7\n  deletion_protection       = true\n  skip_final_snapshot       = false\n  final_snapshot_identifier = \"tokenfly-trading-final\"\n\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading-db\" }\n}\n\n# ── EC2 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndata \"aws_ami\" \"al2023\" {\n  most_recent = true\n  owners      = [\"amazon\"]\n  filter {\n    name   = \"name\"\n    values = [\"al2023-ami-*-x86_64\"]\n  }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_iam_role\" \"ec2\" {\n  name = \"tokenfly-ec2-role\"\n  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({\n    Version = \"2012-10-17\"\n    Statement = [{\n      Action    = \"sts:AssumeRole\"\n      Effect    = \"Allow\"\n      Principal = { Service = \"ec2.amazonaws.com\" }\n    }]\n  })\n}\n\nresource \"aws_iam_role_policy_attachment\" \"ssm\" {\n  role       = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\n  policy_arn = \"arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore\"\n}\n\nresource \"aws_iam_role_policy\" \"ec2_permissions\" {\n  role = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\n  policy = jsonencode({\n    Version = \"2012-10-17\"\n    Statement = [\n      {\n        Effect   = \"Allow\"\n        Action   = [\"secretsmanager:GetSecretValue\"]\n        Resource = [aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.arn]\n      },\n      {\n        Effect   = \"Allow\"\n        Action   = [\"logs:CreateLogGroup\", \"logs:CreateLogStream\", \"logs:PutLogEvents\"]\n        Resource = \"arn:aws:logs:*:*:*\"\n      }\n    ]\n  })\n}\n\nresource \"aws_iam_instance_profile\" \"ec2\" {\n  name = \"tokenfly-ec2-profile\"\n  role = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\n}\n\nresource \"aws_instance\" \"trading\" {\n  ami                    = data.aws_ami.al2023.id\n  instance_type          = \"t3.small\"\n  subnet_id              = aws_subnet.public_a.id\n  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.ec2.id]\n  iam_instance_profile   = aws_iam_instance_profile.ec2.name\n  key_name               = var.key_pair_name\n\n  root_block_device {\n    volume_size = 20\n    volume_type = \"gp3\"\n  }\n\n  user_data = templatefile(\"${path.module}/user_data.sh\", {\n    secret_arn = aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.arn\n    db_host    = aws_db_instance.trading.address\n    db_name    = aws_db_instance.trading.db_name\n    db_user    = aws_db_instance.trading.username\n    aws_region = \"us-east-1\"\n  })\n\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_eip\" \"trading\" {\n  instance = aws_instance.trading.id\n  domain   = \"vpc\"\n}\n\n# ── Secrets Manager ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"random_password\" \"jwt\" {\n  length  = 64\n  special = false\n}\n\nresource \"aws_secretsmanager_secret\" \"trading\" {\n  name                    = \"tokenfly/trading\"\n  recovery_window_in_days = 7\n}\n\nresource \"aws_secretsmanager_secret_version\" \"trading\" {\n  secret_id = aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.id\n  secret_string = jsonencode({\n    KALSHI_API_KEY        = var.kalshi_api_key\n    API_KEY               = var.dashboard_api_key\n    DASHBOARD_API_KEY     = var.dashboard_api_key\n    JWT_SECRET            = random_password.jwt.result\n    DB_PASSWORD           = random_password.db.result\n    TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK = var.trading_alert_webhook\n  })\n}\n\n# ── CloudWatch Log Groups ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_cloudwatch_log_group\" \"pipeline\" {\n  name              = \"/tokenfly/trading/pipeline\"\n  retention_in_days = 30\n}\n\nresource \"aws_cloudwatch_log_group\" \"dashboard\" {\n  name              = \"/tokenfly/trading/dashboard\"\n  retention_in_days = 14\n}\n\n# ── Cost Alert ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_budgets_budget\" \"trading\" {\n  name         = \"tokenfly-trading-monthly\"\n  budget_type  = \"COST\"\n  limit_amount = \"60\"\n  limit_unit   = \"USD\"\n  time_unit    = \"MONTHLY\"\n\n  notification {\n    comparison_operator        = \"GREATER_THAN\"\n    threshold                  = 80\n    threshold_type             = \"PERCENTAGE\"\n    notification_type          = \"ACTUAL\"\n    subscriber_email_addresses = [var.alert_email]\n  }\n}\n\n# ── Variables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nvariable \"kalshi_api_key\"        { sensitive = true }\nvariable \"dashboard_api_key\"     { sensitive = true }\nvariable \"trading_alert_webhook\" { default = \"\" }\nvariable \"key_pair_name\"         { default = \"tokenfly-trading\" }\nvariable \"alert_email\"           {}\nvariable \"allowed_cidr\"          { description = \"Your IP in CIDR: 1.2.3.4/32\" }\n\n# ── Outputs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noutput \"instance_ip\" { value = aws_eip.trading.public_ip }\noutput \"ssh_command\"  { value = \"ssh -i ~/.ssh/${var.key_pair_name}.pem ec2-user@${aws_eip.trading.public_ip}\" }\noutput \"dashboard_url\" { value = \"http://${aws_eip.trading.public_ip}:3199\" }\n```\n\n### 3. EC2 Bootstrap Script (`infrastructure/trading/user_data.sh`)\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\n# Install Docker\ndnf install -y docker aws-cli\nsystemctl enable --now docker\nusermod -aG docker ec2-user\n\n# Docker Compose plugin\nmkdir -p /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins\ncurl -sL \"https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/latest/download/docker-compose-linux-x86_64\" \\\n  -o /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose\nchmod +x /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose\n\n# Fetch secrets from Secrets Manager\nSECRET=$(aws secretsmanager get-secret-value \\\n  --secret-id \"${secret_arn}\" \\\n  --region \"${aws_region}\" \\\n  --query SecretString --output text)\n\n# Parse secret JSON values\nKALSHI_API_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\"    | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['KALSHI_API_KEY'])\")\nAPI_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\"           | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['API_KEY'])\")\nDASHBOARD_API_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\" | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['DASHBOARD_API_KEY'])\")\nJWT_SECRET=$(echo \"$SECRET\"        | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['JWT_SECRET'])\")\nDB_PASSWORD=$(echo \"$SECRET\"       | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['DB_PASSWORD'])\")\nWEBHOOK=$(echo \"$SECRET\"           | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d.get('TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK',''))\")\n\n# Write env file (600 permissions — not world-readable)\nmkdir -p /opt/tokenfly\ncat > /opt/tokenfly/.env <<EOF\nNODE_ENV=production\nPAPER_TRADING=true\n\nKALSHI_API_KEY=$KALSHI_API_KEY\nAPI_KEY=$API_KEY\nDASHBOARD_API_KEY=$DASHBOARD_API_KEY\nJWT_SECRET=$JWT_SECRET\n\nDB_HOST=${db_host}\nDB_PORT=5432\nDB_NAME=${db_name}\nDB_USER=${db_user}\nDB_PASSWORD=$DB_PASSWORD\nPGSSLMODE=require\n\nMAX_POSITION_SIZE=50\nMAX_DAILY_LOSS=200\nMAX_DRAWDOWN=10\nMAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE=500\nMAX_CONCENTRATION=20\n\nTRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK=$WEBHOOK\nEOF\nchmod 600 /opt/tokenfly/.env\n\n# Clone repo (replace with actual repo URL)\ncd /opt/tokenfly\ngit clone https://github.com/tokenflyai/aicompany.git .\n\n# Initialize DB schema\nexport $(grep -v '^#' .env | xargs)\ncd agents/bob/backend\nnode -e \"\n  const {Pool}=require('pg');\n  const fs=require('fs');\n  const pool=new Pool();\n  const sql=fs.readFileSync('db/schema.sql','utf8')\n    +fs.readFileSync('db/schema_strategies.sql','utf8')\n    +fs.readFileSync('db/schema_risk.sql','utf8');\n  pool.query(sql)\n    .then(()=>{console.log('DB init OK');process.exit(0)})\n    .catch(e=>{console.error(e);process.exit(1)});\n\"\ncd /opt/tokenfly\n\n# Start stack\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build\necho \"Tokenfly trading stack started\"\n```\n\n### 4. Production Docker Compose (`docker-compose.prod.yml`)\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"3.9\"\nservices:\n  dashboard:\n    build:\n      context: .\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile\n    container_name: tokenfly-dashboard\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\n    ports:\n      - \"3199:3199\"\n    volumes:\n      - ./agents:/app/agents\n      - ./public:/app/public\n      - /tmp/aicompany_runtime_logs:/tmp/aicompany_runtime_logs\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    logging:\n      driver: awslogs\n      options:\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/dashboard\n        awslogs-region: us-east-1\n        awslogs-stream: dashboard\n\n  trading-api:\n    build:\n      context: ./agents/bob/backend\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile.api\n    container_name: tokenfly-trading-api\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\n    ports:\n      - \"8080:8080\"\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    logging:\n      driver: awslogs\n      options:\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/pipeline\n        awslogs-region: us-east-1\n        awslogs-stream: trading-api\n\n  scheduler:\n    build:\n      context: ./agents/bob/backend\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile.scheduler\n    container_name: tokenfly-scheduler\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    logging:\n      driver: awslogs\n      options:\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/pipeline\n        awslogs-region: us-east-1\n        awslogs-stream: scheduler\n```\n\n### 5. Dockerfiles for Trading Backend\n\n**`agents/bob/backend/Dockerfile.api`**:\n```dockerfile\nFROM node:20-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY package.json package-lock.json ./\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\nCOPY . .\nEXPOSE 8080\nENV PORT=8080\nCMD [\"node\", \"api/server.js\"]\n```\n\n**`agents/bob/backend/Dockerfile.scheduler`**:\n```dockerfile\nFROM node:20-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY package.json package-lock.json ./\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\nCOPY . .\n# Replaces run_scheduler.sh — same 10-minute loop, Docker handles restarts\nCMD [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done\"]\n```\n\n### 6. Terraform Variables (`infrastructure/trading/terraform.tfvars`)\n\n```hcl\n# !! Add to .gitignore — never commit !!\nkalshi_api_key        = \"your-kalshi-api-key\"\ndashboard_api_key     = \"your-dashboard-api-key\"\ntrading_alert_webhook = \"https://hooks.slack.com/services/...\"\nkey_pair_name         = \"tokenfly-trading\"\nalert_email           = \"alerts@tokenfly.ai\"\nallowed_cidr          = \"YOUR_IP/32\"\n```\n\n### 7. Deploy Commands (One-Time)\n\n```bash\n# 1. Create EC2 SSH key pair\naws ec2 create-key-pair \\\n  --key-name tokenfly-trading \\\n  --query 'KeyMaterial' \\\n  --output text > ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem\nchmod 400 ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem\n\n# 2. Create Terraform state bucket\naws s3api create-bucket \\\n  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\\n  --region us-east-1\naws s3api put-bucket-versioning \\\n  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\\n  --versioning-configuration Status=Enabled\n\n# 3. Deploy infrastructure\ncd infrastructure/trading\nterraform init\nterraform plan  -var-file=terraform.tfvars\nterraform apply -var-file=terraform.tfvars\n\n# 4. Verify\nINSTANCE_IP=$(terraform output -raw instance_ip)\ncurl -s http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health        # expect {\"ok\":true,...}\nssh -i ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\\n  \"docker ps\"                                       # expect 3 containers\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables Reference\n\n| Variable | Source | Description |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Kalshi trading API credentials |\n| `API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Dashboard API auth token |\n| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Alias for API_KEY (internal calls) |\n| `JWT_SECRET` | Secrets Manager (auto-generated) | JWT signing key, 64-char random |\n| `DB_HOST` | Terraform output (auto) | RDS endpoint |\n| `DB_PORT` | user_data | `5432` |\n| `DB_NAME` | Terraform (auto) | `kalshi_trading` |\n| `DB_USER` | Terraform (auto) | `trading_user` |\n| `DB_PASSWORD` | Secrets Manager (auto-generated) | RDS password |\n| `PGSSLMODE` | user_data | `require` (RDS enforces TLS) |\n| `PAPER_TRADING` | user_data | `true` — **change to `false` requires Founder approval** |\n| `KALSHI_DEMO` | optional | `1` to use Kalshi demo API instead of live |\n| `MAX_POSITION_SIZE` | user_data | Max contracts per position (50) |\n| `MAX_DAILY_LOSS` | user_data | Daily loss ceiling USD (200) |\n| `MAX_DRAWDOWN` | user_data | Max drawdown % (10) |\n| `MAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE` | user_data | Max total exposure USD (500) |\n| `TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK` | Secrets Manager | Slack/webhook URL for trade alerts |\n| `NODE_ENV` | user_data | `production` |\n\n---\n\n## Scheduler Design\n\n`run_scheduler.sh` runs `live_runner.js` every 10 minutes. The container replaces it:\n\n```dockerfile\nCMD [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done\"]\n```\n\n- `restart: unless-stopped` in Docker Compose handles crashes automatically\n- Logs stream to CloudWatch via `awslogs` driver\n- Future option: AWS EventBridge Scheduler → ECS Fargate task (zero idle cost, no EC2 needed)\n\n---\n\n## Monitoring\n\n### CloudWatch Metric Filter — Pipeline Failures\n\n```bash\naws logs put-metric-filter \\\n  --log-group-name /tokenfly/trading/pipeline \\\n  --filter-name PipelineFailures \\\n  --filter-pattern \"Pipeline FAILED\" \\\n  --metric-transformations \\\n    metricName=PipelineFailures,metricNamespace=Tokenfly,metricValue=1\n```\n\n### CloudWatch Alarm — Alert on Failure\n\n```bash\naws cloudwatch put-metric-alarm \\\n  --alarm-name tokenfly-pipeline-failure \\\n  --metric-name PipelineFailures \\\n  --namespace Tokenfly \\\n  --statistic Sum \\\n  --period 600 \\\n  --threshold 1 \\\n  --comparison-operator GreaterThanOrEqualToThreshold \\\n  --evaluation-periods 1 \\\n  --alarm-actions arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:ACCOUNT:tokenfly-alerts\n```\n\n### Key metrics to watch\n| Metric | Threshold | Action |\n|--------|-----------|--------|\n| Pipeline FAILED in logs | Any occurrence | Page via SNS |\n| EC2 CPUUtilization | > 80% for 5 min | Investigate / upgrade instance |\n| RDS FreeStorageSpace | < 2 GB | Expand allocated storage |\n| Monthly spend | > $48 | Budget alert fires to email |\n\n---\n\n## Monthly Cost Estimate\n\n| Resource | Spec | Cost/month |\n|----------|------|------------|\n| EC2 t3.small | 2 vCPU, 2 GB RAM | ~$15 |\n| RDS db.t3.micro | PostgreSQL 16, 20 GB | ~$17 |\n| EBS gp3 20 GB | EC2 root volume | ~$2 |\n| Elastic IP | Static IP | ~$4 |\n| CloudWatch Logs | ~5 GB/month | ~$3 |\n| Secrets Manager | 1 secret | ~$0.40 |\n| Data transfer | ~10 GB out | ~$1 |\n| **Total** | | **~$42/month** |\n\nCost alert fires at $48 (80% of $60 budget). Defined in Terraform.\n\n**GCP equivalent** (if preferred): `e2-small` (~$13) + Cloud SQL `db-f1-micro` (~$10) + Cloud Logging ≈ $30/month. Same architecture, swap `aws_` providers for `google_` — no application code changes.\n\n---\n\n## Security Notes\n\n1. **Network isolation**: RDS is in private subnets — unreachable from internet. EC2 is the only database client.\n2. **Secrets at rest**: API keys fetched from Secrets Manager at boot, written to `/opt/tokenfly/.env` with `chmod 600`. Rotate by updating the Secrets Manager secret and re-running `user_data.sh` (or SSHing in and restarting containers).\n3. **SSH lockdown**: `allowed_cidr` variable restricts SSH and dashboard access to a single IP. Update after deploy if your IP changes.\n4. **Paper trading gate**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` by default. `live_runner.js` enforces: `const PAPER_TRADING = process.env.PAPER_TRADING !== 'false'`. Flipping to live requires explicit Founder approval (consensus.md entry #1).\n5. **IAM least-privilege**: EC2 role has only `secretsmanager:GetSecretValue` + CloudWatch write. No admin, no S3 read, no EC2 describe.\n\n---\n\n## Rollback\n\n```bash\n# Stop containers only (preserves RDS data)\nssh ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\\n  \"docker compose -f /opt/tokenfly/docker-compose.prod.yml down\"\n\n# Roll back to previous git commit + restart\nssh ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \"cd /opt/tokenfly && git revert HEAD && \\\n  docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build\"\n\n# Destroy all infrastructure (RDS snapshot taken automatically)\ncd infrastructure/trading && terraform destroy -var-file=terraform.tfvars\n```\n\n---\n\n## Day-One Checklist\n\n- [ ] `aws configure` with IAM user (EC2, RDS, Secrets Manager, IAM, S3, Budgets permissions)\n- [ ] Create SSH key pair: `aws ec2 create-key-pair --key-name tokenfly-trading`\n- [ ] Fill in `terraform.tfvars` with real API keys (never commit this file)\n- [ ] `terraform init && terraform apply`\n- [ ] SSH in, verify `docker ps` shows 3 containers running\n- [ ] `curl http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health` returns `{\"ok\":true}`\n- [ ] Tail pipeline log: `docker logs -f tokenfly-scheduler`\n- [ ] Confirm `PAPER_TRADING=true` before any order execution\n- [ ] Set `allowed_cidr` to your real IP in tfvars + `terraform apply`\n\n---\n\n*Quinn — Cloud Engineer | Agent Planet*\n*All infrastructure is code. `infrastructure/trading/` is the source of truth — no manual console changes.*\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":282,"cache_read_input_tokens":42129,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":282},"output_tokens":65,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fce96880-26d9-456d-a3be-a680ae78ce46","uuid":"4770c158-ae37-4d15-89d6-5eb93594cb70"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FJ35ncUACESPEhwXzd6AXT","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/quinn/output/cloud_deployment_plan.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fce96880-26d9-456d-a3be-a680ae78ce46","uuid":"ef9ff136-e405-478e-ae9e-fc878eeb2881","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:36:08.384Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/quinn/output/cloud_deployment_plan.md","content":"# Cloud Deployment Plan — Kalshi Trading Pipeline\n**Author**: Quinn (Cloud Engineer)\n**Task**: T267\n**Date**: 2026-04-03\n**Target**: AWS (primary) with GCP alternative noted\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n                          ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                          │              AWS VPC (us-east-1)         │\n                          │                                           │\n  Internet ───── ALB ──── │ ── EC2 t3.small ───────────────────────  │\n  (HTTPS:443)   (port 80) │   ┌───────────────────────────────────┐  │\n                          │   │  Docker Compose                   │  │\n                          │   │  ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐  │  │\n                          │   │  │  dashboard  │ │  trading-   │  │  │\n                          │   │  │  (port 3199)│ │  api(:8080) │  │  │\n                          │   │  └─────────────┘ └──────┬──────┘  │  │\n                          │   │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n                          │   │  │  scheduler (loop every 10m) │  │  │\n                          │   │  └─────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n                          │   └───────────────────────────────────┘  │\n                          │                    │                       │\n                          │   RDS PostgreSQL ──┘                      │\n                          │   (db.t3.micro, private subnet)           │\n                          └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                      │\n                               Secrets Manager\n                               (KALSHI_API_KEY, DB creds, JWT_SECRET)\n                                      │\n                               CloudWatch Logs\n                               (pipeline + dashboard logs)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Why This Architecture\n\n**Single EC2 + Docker Compose** rather than ECS/EKS:\n- One person can deploy in a day\n- No cluster management overhead\n- The existing `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` work as-is with minor additions\n- Easy SSH access for debugging during early production phase\n- Total cost: ~$42/month (vs $100+/month for ECS Fargate + ALB)\n\n**Upgrade path**: Once trading is proven in production, migrate `trading-api` and `scheduler` to ECS Fargate without changing application code.\n\n---\n\n## Step-by-Step Deployment\n\n### 1. Prerequisites (30 min)\n\n```bash\n# Install AWS CLI + Terraform\nbrew install awscli terraform\naws configure  # region: us-east-1\n```\n\n### 2. Terraform — VPC + EC2 + RDS + Secrets\n\nSave as `infrastructure/trading/main.tf`:\n\n```hcl\nterraform {\n  required_providers {\n    aws = { source = \"hashicorp/aws\", version = \"~> 5.0\" }\n  }\n  backend \"s3\" {\n    bucket = \"tokenfly-tf-state\"\n    key    = \"trading/terraform.tfstate\"\n    region = \"us-east-1\"\n  }\n}\n\nprovider \"aws\" { region = \"us-east-1\" }\n\n# ── VPC ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_vpc\" \"trading\" {\n  cidr_block           = \"10.0.0.0/16\"\n  enable_dns_hostnames = true\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_internet_gateway\" \"igw\" {\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\n}\n\nresource \"aws_subnet\" \"public_a\" {\n  vpc_id                  = aws_vpc.trading.id\n  cidr_block              = \"10.0.1.0/24\"\n  availability_zone       = \"us-east-1a\"\n  map_public_ip_on_launch = true\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-public-a\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_subnet\" \"private_a\" {\n  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.trading.id\n  cidr_block        = \"10.0.10.0/24\"\n  availability_zone = \"us-east-1a\"\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-private-a\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_subnet\" \"private_b\" {\n  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.trading.id\n  cidr_block        = \"10.0.11.0/24\"\n  availability_zone = \"us-east-1b\"\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-private-b\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_route_table\" \"public\" {\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\n  route {\n    cidr_block = \"0.0.0.0/0\"\n    gateway_id = aws_internet_gateway.igw.id\n  }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_route_table_association\" \"public_a\" {\n  subnet_id      = aws_subnet.public_a.id\n  route_table_id = aws_route_table.public.id\n}\n\n# ── Security Groups ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_security_group\" \"ec2\" {\n  name   = \"tokenfly-ec2\"\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\n\n  ingress {\n    description = \"Dashboard\"\n    from_port   = 3199\n    to_port     = 3199\n    protocol    = \"tcp\"\n    cidr_blocks = [var.allowed_cidr]   # Set to your IP: \"1.2.3.4/32\"\n  }\n  ingress {\n    description = \"SSH\"\n    from_port   = 22\n    to_port     = 22\n    protocol    = \"tcp\"\n    cidr_blocks = [var.allowed_cidr]\n  }\n  egress {\n    from_port   = 0\n    to_port     = 0\n    protocol    = \"-1\"\n    cidr_blocks = [\"0.0.0.0/0\"]\n  }\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-ec2-sg\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_security_group\" \"rds\" {\n  name   = \"tokenfly-rds\"\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\n\n  ingress {\n    description     = \"Postgres from EC2 only\"\n    from_port       = 5432\n    to_port         = 5432\n    protocol        = \"tcp\"\n    security_groups = [aws_security_group.ec2.id]\n  }\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-rds-sg\" }\n}\n\n# ── RDS PostgreSQL ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_db_subnet_group\" \"trading\" {\n  name       = \"tokenfly-trading\"\n  subnet_ids = [aws_subnet.private_a.id, aws_subnet.private_b.id]\n}\n\nresource \"random_password\" \"db\" {\n  length  = 32\n  special = false\n}\n\nresource \"aws_db_instance\" \"trading\" {\n  identifier        = \"tokenfly-trading\"\n  engine            = \"postgres\"\n  engine_version    = \"16.3\"\n  instance_class    = \"db.t3.micro\"\n  allocated_storage = 20\n  storage_type      = \"gp2\"\n\n  db_name  = \"kalshi_trading\"\n  username = \"trading_user\"\n  password = random_password.db.result\n\n  db_subnet_group_name   = aws_db_subnet_group.trading.name\n  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.rds.id]\n\n  backup_retention_period   = 7\n  deletion_protection       = true\n  skip_final_snapshot       = false\n  final_snapshot_identifier = \"tokenfly-trading-final\"\n\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading-db\" }\n}\n\n# ── EC2 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndata \"aws_ami\" \"al2023\" {\n  most_recent = true\n  owners      = [\"amazon\"]\n  filter {\n    name   = \"name\"\n    values = [\"al2023-ami-*-x86_64\"]\n  }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_iam_role\" \"ec2\" {\n  name = \"tokenfly-ec2-role\"\n  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({\n    Version = \"2012-10-17\"\n    Statement = [{\n      Action    = \"sts:AssumeRole\"\n      Effect    = \"Allow\"\n      Principal = { Service = \"ec2.amazonaws.com\" }\n    }]\n  })\n}\n\nresource \"aws_iam_role_policy_attachment\" \"ssm\" {\n  role       = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\n  policy_arn = \"arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore\"\n}\n\nresource \"aws_iam_role_policy\" \"ec2_permissions\" {\n  role = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\n  policy = jsonencode({\n    Version = \"2012-10-17\"\n    Statement = [\n      {\n        Effect   = \"Allow\"\n        Action   = [\"secretsmanager:GetSecretValue\"]\n        Resource = [aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.arn]\n      },\n      {\n        Effect   = \"Allow\"\n        Action   = [\"logs:CreateLogGroup\", \"logs:CreateLogStream\", \"logs:PutLogEvents\"]\n        Resource = \"arn:aws:logs:*:*:*\"\n      }\n    ]\n  })\n}\n\nresource \"aws_iam_instance_profile\" \"ec2\" {\n  name = \"tokenfly-ec2-profile\"\n  role = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\n}\n\nresource \"aws_instance\" \"trading\" {\n  ami                    = data.aws_ami.al2023.id\n  instance_type          = \"t3.small\"\n  subnet_id              = aws_subnet.public_a.id\n  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.ec2.id]\n  iam_instance_profile   = aws_iam_instance_profile.ec2.name\n  key_name               = var.key_pair_name\n\n  root_block_device {\n    volume_size = 20\n    volume_type = \"gp3\"\n  }\n\n  user_data = templatefile(\"${path.module}/user_data.sh\", {\n    secret_arn = aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.arn\n    db_host    = aws_db_instance.trading.address\n    db_name    = aws_db_instance.trading.db_name\n    db_user    = aws_db_instance.trading.username\n    aws_region = \"us-east-1\"\n  })\n\n  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading\" }\n}\n\nresource \"aws_eip\" \"trading\" {\n  instance = aws_instance.trading.id\n  domain   = \"vpc\"\n}\n\n# ── Secrets Manager ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"random_password\" \"jwt\" {\n  length  = 64\n  special = false\n}\n\nresource \"aws_secretsmanager_secret\" \"trading\" {\n  name                    = \"tokenfly/trading\"\n  recovery_window_in_days = 7\n}\n\nresource \"aws_secretsmanager_secret_version\" \"trading\" {\n  secret_id = aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.id\n  secret_string = jsonencode({\n    KALSHI_API_KEY        = var.kalshi_api_key\n    API_KEY               = var.dashboard_api_key\n    DASHBOARD_API_KEY     = var.dashboard_api_key\n    JWT_SECRET            = random_password.jwt.result\n    DB_PASSWORD           = random_password.db.result\n    TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK = var.trading_alert_webhook\n  })\n}\n\n# ── CloudWatch Log Groups ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_cloudwatch_log_group\" \"pipeline\" {\n  name              = \"/tokenfly/trading/pipeline\"\n  retention_in_days = 30\n}\n\nresource \"aws_cloudwatch_log_group\" \"dashboard\" {\n  name              = \"/tokenfly/trading/dashboard\"\n  retention_in_days = 14\n}\n\n# ── Cost Alert ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nresource \"aws_budgets_budget\" \"trading\" {\n  name         = \"tokenfly-trading-monthly\"\n  budget_type  = \"COST\"\n  limit_amount = \"60\"\n  limit_unit   = \"USD\"\n  time_unit    = \"MONTHLY\"\n\n  notification {\n    comparison_operator        = \"GREATER_THAN\"\n    threshold                  = 80\n    threshold_type             = \"PERCENTAGE\"\n    notification_type          = \"ACTUAL\"\n    subscriber_email_addresses = [var.alert_email]\n  }\n}\n\n# ── Variables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nvariable \"kalshi_api_key\"        { sensitive = true }\nvariable \"dashboard_api_key\"     { sensitive = true }\nvariable \"trading_alert_webhook\" { default = \"\" }\nvariable \"key_pair_name\"         { default = \"tokenfly-trading\" }\nvariable \"alert_email\"           {}\nvariable \"allowed_cidr\"          { description = \"Your IP in CIDR: 1.2.3.4/32\" }\n\n# ── Outputs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noutput \"instance_ip\" { value = aws_eip.trading.public_ip }\noutput \"ssh_command\"  { value = \"ssh -i ~/.ssh/${var.key_pair_name}.pem ec2-user@${aws_eip.trading.public_ip}\" }\noutput \"dashboard_url\" { value = \"http://${aws_eip.trading.public_ip}:3199\" }\n```\n\n### 3. EC2 Bootstrap Script (`infrastructure/trading/user_data.sh`)\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\n# Install Docker\ndnf install -y docker aws-cli\nsystemctl enable --now docker\nusermod -aG docker ec2-user\n\n# Docker Compose plugin\nmkdir -p /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins\ncurl -sL \"https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/latest/download/docker-compose-linux-x86_64\" \\\n  -o /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose\nchmod +x /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose\n\n# Fetch secrets from Secrets Manager\nSECRET=$(aws secretsmanager get-secret-value \\\n  --secret-id \"${secret_arn}\" \\\n  --region \"${aws_region}\" \\\n  --query SecretString --output text)\n\n# Parse secret JSON values\nKALSHI_API_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\"    | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['KALSHI_API_KEY'])\")\nAPI_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\"           | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['API_KEY'])\")\nDASHBOARD_API_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\" | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['DASHBOARD_API_KEY'])\")\nJWT_SECRET=$(echo \"$SECRET\"        | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['JWT_SECRET'])\")\nDB_PASSWORD=$(echo \"$SECRET\"       | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['DB_PASSWORD'])\")\nWEBHOOK=$(echo \"$SECRET\"           | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d.get('TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK',''))\")\n\n# Write env file (600 permissions — not world-readable)\nmkdir -p /opt/tokenfly\ncat > /opt/tokenfly/.env <<EOF\nNODE_ENV=production\nPAPER_TRADING=true\n\nKALSHI_API_KEY=$KALSHI_API_KEY\nAPI_KEY=$API_KEY\nDASHBOARD_API_KEY=$DASHBOARD_API_KEY\nJWT_SECRET=$JWT_SECRET\n\nDB_HOST=${db_host}\nDB_PORT=5432\nDB_NAME=${db_name}\nDB_USER=${db_user}\nDB_PASSWORD=$DB_PASSWORD\nPGSSLMODE=require\n\nMAX_POSITION_SIZE=50\nMAX_DAILY_LOSS=200\nMAX_DRAWDOWN=10\nMAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE=500\nMAX_CONCENTRATION=20\n\nTRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK=$WEBHOOK\nEOF\nchmod 600 /opt/tokenfly/.env\n\n# Clone repo (replace with actual repo URL)\ncd /opt/tokenfly\ngit clone https://github.com/tokenflyai/aicompany.git .\n\n# Initialize DB schema\nexport $(grep -v '^#' .env | xargs)\ncd agents/bob/backend\nnode -e \"\n  const {Pool}=require('pg');\n  const fs=require('fs');\n  const pool=new Pool();\n  const sql=fs.readFileSync('db/schema.sql','utf8')\n    +fs.readFileSync('db/schema_strategies.sql','utf8')\n    +fs.readFileSync('db/schema_risk.sql','utf8');\n  pool.query(sql)\n    .then(()=>{console.log('DB init OK');process.exit(0)})\n    .catch(e=>{console.error(e);process.exit(1)});\n\"\ncd /opt/tokenfly\n\n# Start stack\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build\necho \"Tokenfly trading stack started\"\n```\n\n### 4. Production Docker Compose (`docker-compose.prod.yml`)\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"3.9\"\nservices:\n  dashboard:\n    build:\n      context: .\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile\n    container_name: tokenfly-dashboard\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\n    ports:\n      - \"3199:3199\"\n    volumes:\n      - ./agents:/app/agents\n      - ./public:/app/public\n      - /tmp/aicompany_runtime_logs:/tmp/aicompany_runtime_logs\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    logging:\n      driver: awslogs\n      options:\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/dashboard\n        awslogs-region: us-east-1\n        awslogs-stream: dashboard\n\n  trading-api:\n    build:\n      context: ./agents/bob/backend\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile.api\n    container_name: tokenfly-trading-api\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\n    ports:\n      - \"8080:8080\"\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    logging:\n      driver: awslogs\n      options:\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/pipeline\n        awslogs-region: us-east-1\n        awslogs-stream: trading-api\n\n  scheduler:\n    build:\n      context: ./agents/bob/backend\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile.scheduler\n    container_name: tokenfly-scheduler\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    logging:\n      driver: awslogs\n      options:\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/pipeline\n        awslogs-region: us-east-1\n        awslogs-stream: scheduler\n```\n\n### 5. Dockerfiles for Trading Backend\n\n**`agents/bob/backend/Dockerfile.api`**:\n```dockerfile\nFROM node:20-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY package.json package-lock.json ./\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\nCOPY . .\nEXPOSE 8080\nENV PORT=8080\nCMD [\"node\", \"api/server.js\"]\n```\n\n**`agents/bob/backend/Dockerfile.scheduler`**:\n```dockerfile\nFROM node:20-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY package.json package-lock.json ./\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\nCOPY . .\n# Replaces run_scheduler.sh — same 10-minute loop, Docker handles restarts\nCMD [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done\"]\n```\n\n### 6. Terraform Variables (`infrastructure/trading/terraform.tfvars`)\n\n```hcl\n# !! Add to .gitignore — never commit !!\nkalshi_api_key        = \"your-kalshi-api-key\"\ndashboard_api_key     = \"your-dashboard-api-key\"\ntrading_alert_webhook = \"https://hooks.slack.com/services/...\"\nkey_pair_name         = \"tokenfly-trading\"\nalert_email           = \"alerts@tokenfly.ai\"\nallowed_cidr          = \"YOUR_IP/32\"\n```\n\n### 7. Deploy Commands (One-Time)\n\n```bash\n# 1. Create EC2 SSH key pair\naws ec2 create-key-pair \\\n  --key-name tokenfly-trading \\\n  --query 'KeyMaterial' \\\n  --output text > ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem\nchmod 400 ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem\n\n# 2. Create Terraform state bucket\naws s3api create-bucket \\\n  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\\n  --region us-east-1\naws s3api put-bucket-versioning \\\n  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\\n  --versioning-configuration Status=Enabled\n\n# 3. Deploy infrastructure\ncd infrastructure/trading\nterraform init\nterraform plan  -var-file=terraform.tfvars\nterraform apply -var-file=terraform.tfvars\n\n# 4. Verify\nINSTANCE_IP=$(terraform output -raw instance_ip)\ncurl -s http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health        # expect {\"ok\":true,...}\nssh -i ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\\n  \"docker ps\"                                       # expect 3 containers\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables Reference\n\n| Variable | Source | Description |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Kalshi trading API credentials |\n| `API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Dashboard API auth token |\n| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Alias for API_KEY (internal calls) |\n| `JWT_SECRET` | Secrets Manager (auto-generated) | JWT signing key, 64-char random |\n| `DB_HOST` | Terraform output (auto) | RDS endpoint |\n| `DB_PORT` | user_data | `5432` |\n| `DB_NAME` | Terraform (auto) | `kalshi_trading` |\n| `DB_USER` | Terraform (auto) | `trading_user` |\n| `DB_PASSWORD` | Secrets Manager (auto-generated) | RDS password |\n| `PGSSLMODE` | user_data | `require` (RDS enforces TLS) |\n| `PAPER_TRADING` | user_data | `true` — **change to `false` requires Founder approval** |\n| `KALSHI_DEMO` | optional | `1` to use Kalshi demo API instead of live |\n| `MAX_POSITION_SIZE` | user_data | Max contracts per position (50) |\n| `MAX_DAILY_LOSS` | user_data | Daily loss ceiling USD (200) |\n| `MAX_DRAWDOWN` | user_data | Max drawdown % (10) |\n| `MAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE` | user_data | Max total exposure USD (500) |\n| `TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK` | Secrets Manager | Slack/webhook URL for trade alerts |\n| `NODE_ENV` | user_data | `production` |\n\n---\n\n## Scheduler Design\n\n`run_scheduler.sh` runs `live_runner.js` every 10 minutes. The container replaces it:\n\n```dockerfile\nCMD [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done\"]\n```\n\n- `restart: unless-stopped` in Docker Compose handles crashes automatically\n- Logs stream to CloudWatch via `awslogs` driver\n- Future option: AWS EventBridge Scheduler → ECS Fargate task (zero idle cost, no EC2 needed)\n\n---\n\n## Monitoring\n\n### CloudWatch Metric Filter — Pipeline Failures\n\n```bash\naws logs put-metric-filter \\\n  --log-group-name /tokenfly/trading/pipeline \\\n  --filter-name PipelineFailures \\\n  --filter-pattern \"Pipeline FAILED\" \\\n  --metric-transformations \\\n    metricName=PipelineFailures,metricNamespace=Tokenfly,metricValue=1\n```\n\n### CloudWatch Alarm — Alert on Failure\n\n```bash\naws cloudwatch put-metric-alarm \\\n  --alarm-name tokenfly-pipeline-failure \\\n  --metric-name PipelineFailures \\\n  --namespace Tokenfly \\\n  --statistic Sum \\\n  --period 600 \\\n  --threshold 1 \\\n  --comparison-operator GreaterThanOrEqualToThreshold \\\n  --evaluation-periods 1 \\\n  --alarm-actions arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:ACCOUNT:tokenfly-alerts\n```\n\n### Key metrics to watch\n| Metric | Threshold | Action |\n|--------|-----------|--------|\n| Pipeline FAILED in logs | Any occurrence | Page via SNS |\n| EC2 CPUUtilization | > 80% for 5 min | Investigate / upgrade instance |\n| RDS FreeStorageSpace | < 2 GB | Expand allocated storage |\n| Monthly spend | > $48 | Budget alert fires to email |\n\n---\n\n## Monthly Cost Estimate\n\n| Resource | Spec | Cost/month |\n|----------|------|------------|\n| EC2 t3.small | 2 vCPU, 2 GB RAM | ~$15 |\n| RDS db.t3.micro | PostgreSQL 16, 20 GB | ~$17 |\n| EBS gp3 20 GB | EC2 root volume | ~$2 |\n| Elastic IP | Static IP | ~$4 |\n| CloudWatch Logs | ~5 GB/month | ~$3 |\n| Secrets Manager | 1 secret | ~$0.40 |\n| Data transfer | ~10 GB out | ~$1 |\n| **Total** | | **~$42/month** |\n\nCost alert fires at $48 (80% of $60 budget). Defined in Terraform.\n\n**GCP equivalent** (if preferred): `e2-small` (~$13) + Cloud SQL `db-f1-micro` (~$10) + Cloud Logging ≈ $30/month. Same architecture, swap `aws_` providers for `google_` — no application code changes.\n\n---\n\n## Security Notes\n\n1. **Network isolation**: RDS is in private subnets — unreachable from internet. EC2 is the only database client.\n2. **Secrets at rest**: API keys fetched from Secrets Manager at boot, written to `/opt/tokenfly/.env` with `chmod 600`. Rotate by updating the Secrets Manager secret and re-running `user_data.sh` (or SSHing in and restarting containers).\n3. **SSH lockdown**: `allowed_cidr` variable restricts SSH and dashboard access to a single IP. Update after deploy if your IP changes.\n4. **Paper trading gate**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` by default. `live_runner.js` enforces: `const PAPER_TRADING = process.env.PAPER_TRADING !== 'false'`. Flipping to live requires explicit Founder approval (consensus.md entry #1).\n5. **IAM least-privilege**: EC2 role has only `secretsmanager:GetSecretValue` + CloudWatch write. No admin, no S3 read, no EC2 describe.\n\n---\n\n## Rollback\n\n```bash\n# Stop containers only (preserves RDS data)\nssh ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\\n  \"docker compose -f /opt/tokenfly/docker-compose.prod.yml down\"\n\n# Roll back to previous git commit + restart\nssh ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \"cd /opt/tokenfly && git revert HEAD && \\\n  docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build\"\n\n# Destroy all infrastructure (RDS snapshot taken automatically)\ncd infrastructure/trading && terraform destroy -var-file=terraform.tfvars\n```\n\n---\n\n## Day-One Checklist\n\n- [ ] `aws configure` with IAM user (EC2, RDS, Secrets Manager, IAM, S3, Budgets permissions)\n- [ ] Create SSH key pair: `aws ec2 create-key-pair --key-name tokenfly-trading`\n- [ ] Fill in `terraform.tfvars` with real API keys (never commit this file)\n- [ ] `terraform init && terraform apply`\n- [ ] SSH in, verify `docker ps` shows 3 containers running\n- [ ] `curl http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health` returns `{\"ok\":true}`\n- [ ] Tail pipeline log: `docker logs -f tokenfly-scheduler`\n- [ ] Confirm `PAPER_TRADING=true` before any order execution\n- [ ] Set `allowed_cidr` to your real IP in tfvars + `terraform apply`\n\n---\n\n*Quinn — Cloud Engineer | Agent Planet*\n*All infrastructure is code. `infrastructure/trading/` is the source of truth — no manual console changes.*\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":2,"oldLines":410,"newStart":2,"newLines":695,"lines":[" **Author**: Quinn (Cloud Engineer)"," **Task**: T267"," **Date**: 2026-04-03","-**Target**: AWS (primary) with GCP notes where applicable","+**Target**: AWS (primary) with GCP alternative noted"," "," ---"," ","-## Overview","+## Architecture Overview"," ","-Deploy the Kalshi trading pipeline as a containerized workload on AWS. The system consists of three processes:","+```","+                          ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐","+                          │              AWS VPC (us-east-1)         │","+                          │                                           │","+  Internet ───── ALB ──── │ ── EC2 t3.small ───────────────────────  │","+  (HTTPS:443)   (port 80) │   ┌───────────────────────────────────┐  │","+                          │   │  Docker Compose                   │  │","+                          │   │  ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐  │  │","+                          │   │  │  dashboard  │ │  trading-   │  │  │","+                          │   │  │  (port 3199)│ │  api(:8080) │  │  │","+                          │   │  └─────────────┘ └──────┬──────┘  │  │","+                          │   │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐  │  │","+                          │   │  │  scheduler (loop every 10m) │  │  │","+                          │   │  └─────────────────────────────┘  │  │","+                          │   └───────────────────────────────────┘  │","+                          │                    │                       │","+                          │   RDS PostgreSQL ──┘                      │","+                          │   (db.t3.micro, private subnet)           │","+                          └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘","+                                      │","+                               Secrets Manager","+                               (KALSHI_API_KEY, DB creds, JWT_SECRET)","+                                      │","+                               CloudWatch Logs","+                               (pipeline + dashboard logs)","+```"," ","-| Process | Source | Port | Description |","-|---------|--------|------|-------------|","-| `kalshi-dashboard` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js` | 3200 | Trade signals API |","-| `kalshi-scheduler` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard/run_scheduler.sh` | — | Runs `live_runner.js` every 10 min |","-| `kalshi-monitor` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard/monitor.js` | — | Alerts if pipeline stalls |","+---"," ","-A one-person operator can deploy this in a single day following the steps below.","+## Why This Architecture"," ","+**Single EC2 + Docker Compose** rather than ECS/EKS:","+- One person can deploy in a day","+- No cluster management overhead","+- The existing `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` work as-is with minor additions","+- Easy SSH access for debugging during early production phase","+- Total cost: ~$42/month (vs $100+/month for ECS Fargate + ALB)","+","+**Upgrade path**: Once trading is proven in production, migrate `trading-api` and `scheduler` to ECS Fargate without changing application code.","+"," ---"," ","-## Architecture","+## Step-by-Step Deployment"," ","+### 1. Prerequisites (30 min)","+","+```bash","+# Install AWS CLI + Terraform","+brew install awscli terraform","+aws configure  # region: us-east-1"," ```","-Internet","-    │","-    ▼","-Route 53 (optional domain)","-    │","-    ▼","-ALB (HTTPS :443 → HTTP :3200)","-    │","-    ▼","-ECS Fargate Task (trading-pipeline)","-  ├── kalshi-dashboard    :3200","-  ├── kalshi-scheduler    (no port — cron loop)","-  └── kalshi-monitor      (no port — polling loop)","-    │","-    ▼","-AWS Secrets Manager","-  └── KALSHI_API_KEY, DASHBOARD_API_KEY","-```"," ","-No database required. Trade signals are written to JSON files; PnL state is file-based. EFS mounts the `agents/bob/output/` directory for persistence across task restarts.","+### 2. Terraform — VPC + EC2 + RDS + Secrets"," ","-**Monthly cost estimate** (us-east-1, on-demand):","-| Resource | Config | $/month |","-|----------|--------|---------|","-| ECS Fargate | 0.25 vCPU / 512 MB, 24×7 | ~$9 |","-| ALB | 1 instance | ~$18 |","-| EFS | < 1 GB | < $1 |","-| Secrets Manager | 2 secrets | $0.80 |","-| CloudWatch Logs | ~1 GB/mo | ~$0.50 |","-| **Total** | | **~$29/month** |","+Save as `infrastructure/trading/main.tf`:"," ","-To cut cost to ~$11/month: drop the ALB and expose the dashboard directly (no HTTPS) — acceptable for a single-operator internal tool.","+```hcl","+terraform {","+  required_providers {","+    aws = { source = \"hashicorp/aws\", version = \"~> 5.0\" }","+  }","+  backend \"s3\" {","+    bucket = \"tokenfly-tf-state\"","+    key    = \"trading/terraform.tfstate\"","+    region = \"us-east-1\"","+  }","+}"," ","----","+provider \"aws\" { region = \"us-east-1\" }"," ","-## Container Choice: AWS Fargate","+# ── VPC ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+resource \"aws_vpc\" \"trading\" {","+  cidr_block           = \"10.0.0.0/16\"","+  enable_dns_hostnames = true","+  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading\" }","+}"," ","-**Why Fargate over EC2:**","-- No instance management, patching, or AMI rotation","-- Scales to zero when stopped; billing is per-second","-- Sufficient for a single trading pipeline (scheduler runs every 10 min, CPU burst only)","+resource \"aws_internet_gateway\" \"igw\" {","+  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id","+}"," ","-**Why not Lambda:**","-- The scheduler is a `while true; sleep 600` loop — Lambda's max execution time (15 min) doesn't fit","-- live_runner.js needs persistent file output between runs","+resource \"aws_subnet\" \"public_a\" {","+  vpc_id                  = aws_vpc.trading.id","+  cidr_block              = \"10.0.1.0/24\"","+  availability_zone       = \"us-east-1a\"","+  map_public_ip_on_launch = true","+  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-public-a\" }","+}"," ","-**Why not GCP Cloud Run:**","-- Existing Terraform modules are AWS-native (ECS, ALB, EFS, Secrets Manager)","-- Switch to GCP Cloud Run only if Kalshi API latency to GCP us-central1 is significantly better","+resource \"aws_subnet\" \"private_a\" {","+  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.trading.id","+  cidr_block        = \"10.0.10.0/24\"","+  availability_zone = \"us-east-1a\"","+  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-private-a\" }","+}"," ","----","+resource \"aws_subnet\" \"private_b\" {","+  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.trading.id","+  cidr_block        = \"10.0.11.0/24\"","+  availability_zone = \"us-east-1b\"","+  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-private-b\" }","+}"," ","-## Environment Variables","+resource \"aws_route_table\" \"public\" {","+  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id","+  route {","+    cidr_block = \"0.0.0.0/0\"","+    gateway_id = aws_internet_gateway.igw.id","+  }","+}"," ","-Injected at runtime from **AWS Secrets Manager** — never hardcoded in container or task definition.","+resource \"aws_route_table_association\" \"public_a\" {","+  subnet_id      = aws_subnet.public_a.id","+  route_table_id = aws_route_table.public.id","+}"," ","-| Variable | Required | Description |","-|----------|----------|-------------|","-| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Yes (live trading) | Kalshi REST API key — obtain from kalshi.com |","-| `KALSHI_DEMO` | No | `\"false\"` = live mode; default = demo/paper mode |","-| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | Yes (production) | Bearer token for `/api/*` auth on port 3200 |","-| `PAPER_TRADING` | No | Default `true` — set `\"false\"` only after founder approval |","-| `NODE_ENV` | Yes | `\"production\"` |","-| `PORT` | Yes | `3200` (dashboard API) |","+# ── Security Groups ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+resource \"aws_security_group\" \"ec2\" {","+  name   = \"tokenfly-ec2\"","+  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id"," ","-**Critical**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` is the default and must remain so until founder explicitly approves live order submission (per team consensus rule #1).","+  ingress {","+    description = \"Dashboard\"","+    from_port   = 3199","+    to_port     = 3199","+    protocol    = \"tcp\"","+    cidr_blocks = [var.allowed_cidr]   # Set to your IP: \"1.2.3.4/32\"","+  }","+  ingress {","+    description = \"SSH\"","+    from_port   = 22","+    to_port     = 22","+    protocol    = \"tcp\"","+    cidr_blocks = [var.allowed_cidr]","+  }","+  egress {","+    from_port   = 0","+    to_port     = 0","+    protocol    = \"-1\"","+    cidr_blocks = [\"0.0.0.0/0\"]","+  }","+  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-ec2-sg\" }","+}"," ","-### Secrets Manager setup (one-time)","-```bash","-# Create secrets","-aws secretsmanager create-secret \\","-  --name \"tokenfly/trading/kalshi-api-key\" \\","-  --secret-string \"YOUR_KALSHI_API_KEY\"","+resource \"aws_security_group\" \"rds\" {","+  name   = \"tokenfly-rds\"","+  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id"," ","-aws secretsmanager create-secret \\","-  --name \"tokenfly/trading/dashboard-api-key\" \\","-  --secret-string \"$(openssl rand -hex 32)\"","-```","+  ingress {","+    description     = \"Postgres from EC2 only\"","+    from_port       = 5432","+    to_port         = 5432","+    protocol        = \"tcp\"","+    security_groups = [aws_security_group.ec2.id]","+  }","+  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-rds-sg\" }","+}"," ","----","+# ── RDS PostgreSQL ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+resource \"aws_db_subnet_group\" \"trading\" {","+  name       = \"tokenfly-trading\"","+  subnet_ids = [aws_subnet.private_a.id, aws_subnet.private_b.id]","+}"," ","-## Deployment Steps (Day 1)","+resource \"random_password\" \"db\" {","+  length  = 32","+  special = false","+}"," ","-### Prerequisites","-- AWS account with CLI configured (`aws configure`)","-- Docker installed locally","-- Terraform >= 1.6","-- Node.js 20 (for local build/test)","+resource \"aws_db_instance\" \"trading\" {","+  identifier        = \"tokenfly-trading\"","+  engine            = \"postgres\"","+  engine_version    = \"16.3\"","+  instance_class    = \"db.t3.micro\"","+  allocated_storage = 20","+  storage_type      = \"gp2\""," ","-### Step 1: Build and push container image (~15 min)","+  db_name  = \"kalshi_trading\"","+  username = \"trading_user\"","+  password = random_password.db.result"," ","-```bash","-# From aicompany/ root","-cd /path/to/aicompany","+  db_subnet_group_name   = aws_db_subnet_group.trading.name","+  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.rds.id]"," ","-# Create ECR repo (one-time)","-aws ecr create-repository --repository-name tokenfly-trading --region us-east-1","+  backup_retention_period   = 7","+  deletion_protection       = true","+  skip_final_snapshot       = false","+  final_snapshot_identifier = \"tokenfly-trading-final\""," ","-# Authenticate Docker to ECR","-aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 \\","-  | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin \\","-    <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com","+  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading-db\" }","+}"," ","-# Build trading pipeline image","-docker build -f Dockerfile.trading -t tokenfly-trading:latest .","+# ── EC2 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+data \"aws_ami\" \"al2023\" {","+  most_recent = true","+  owners      = [\"amazon\"]","+  filter {","+    name   = \"name\"","+    values = [\"al2023-ami-*-x86_64\"]","+  }","+}"," ","-# Tag and push","-docker tag tokenfly-trading:latest \\","-  <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/tokenfly-trading:latest","-docker push <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/tokenfly-trading:latest","-```","+resource \"aws_iam_role\" \"ec2\" {","+  name = \"tokenfly-ec2-role\"","+  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({","+    Version = \"2012-10-17\"","+    Statement = [{","+      Action    = \"sts:AssumeRole\"","+      Effect    = \"Allow\"","+      Principal = { Service = \"ec2.amazonaws.com\" }","+    }]","+  })","+}"," ","-### Step 2: Create Dockerfile.trading","+resource \"aws_iam_role_policy_attachment\" \"ssm\" {","+  role       = aws_iam_role.ec2.name","+  policy_arn = \"arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore\"","+}"," ","-The existing `Dockerfile` serves the agent dashboard. The trading pipeline needs its own image:","+resource \"aws_iam_role_policy\" \"ec2_permissions\" {","+  role = aws_iam_role.ec2.name","+  policy = jsonencode({","+    Version = \"2012-10-17\"","+    Statement = [","+      {","+        Effect   = \"Allow\"","+        Action   = [\"secretsmanager:GetSecretValue\"]","+        Resource = [aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.arn]","+      },","+      {","+        Effect   = \"Allow\"","+        Action   = [\"logs:CreateLogGroup\", \"logs:CreateLogStream\", \"logs:PutLogEvents\"]","+        Resource = \"arn:aws:logs:*:*:*\"","+      }","+    ]","+  })","+}"," ","-```dockerfile","-# Dockerfile.trading","-FROM node:20-alpine","+resource \"aws_iam_instance_profile\" \"ec2\" {","+  name = \"tokenfly-ec2-profile\"","+  role = aws_iam_role.ec2.name","+}"," ","-RUN apk add --no-cache bash","+resource \"aws_instance\" \"trading\" {","+  ami                    = data.aws_ami.al2023.id","+  instance_type          = \"t3.small\"","+  subnet_id              = aws_subnet.public_a.id","+  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.ec2.id]","+  iam_instance_profile   = aws_iam_instance_profile.ec2.name","+  key_name               = var.key_pair_name"," ","-WORKDIR /app","+  root_block_device {","+    volume_size = 20","+    volume_type = \"gp3\"","+  }"," ","-# Install production deps","-COPY agents/bob/backend/package.json agents/bob/backend/package-lock.json ./","-RUN npm ci --omit=dev","+  user_data = templatefile(\"${path.module}/user_data.sh\", {","+    secret_arn = aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.arn","+    db_host    = aws_db_instance.trading.address","+    db_name    = aws_db_instance.trading.db_name","+    db_user    = aws_db_instance.trading.username","+    aws_region = \"us-east-1\"","+  })"," ","-# Copy trading pipeline source","-COPY agents/bob/backend/ ./","+  tags = { Name = \"tokenfly-trading\" }","+}"," ","-# Create output directory for trade signals","-RUN mkdir -p /app/output","+resource \"aws_eip\" \"trading\" {","+  instance = aws_instance.trading.id","+  domain   = \"vpc\"","+}"," ","-EXPOSE 3200","+# ── Secrets Manager ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+resource \"random_password\" \"jwt\" {","+  length  = 64","+  special = false","+}"," ","-ENV NODE_ENV=production \\","-    PORT=3200 \\","-    PAPER_TRADING=true","+resource \"aws_secretsmanager_secret\" \"trading\" {","+  name                    = \"tokenfly/trading\"","+  recovery_window_in_days = 7","+}"," ","-# Start all three processes via PM2","-RUN npm install -g pm2","-CMD [\"pm2-runtime\", \"ecosystem.trading.config.js\"]","-```","+resource \"aws_secretsmanager_secret_version\" \"trading\" {","+  secret_id = aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.id","+  secret_string = jsonencode({","+    KALSHI_API_KEY        = var.kalshi_api_key","+    API_KEY               = var.dashboard_api_key","+    DASHBOARD_API_KEY     = var.dashboard_api_key","+    JWT_SECRET            = random_password.jwt.result","+    DB_PASSWORD           = random_password.db.result","+    TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK = var.trading_alert_webhook","+  })","+}"," ","-### Step 3: Create PM2 config for trading processes","+# ── CloudWatch Log Groups ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+resource \"aws_cloudwatch_log_group\" \"pipeline\" {","+  name              = \"/tokenfly/trading/pipeline\"","+  retention_in_days = 30","+}"," ","-```javascript","-// ecosystem.trading.config.js","-module.exports = {","-  apps: [","-    {","-      name: \"kalshi-dashboard\",","-      script: \"dashboard_api.js\",","-      instances: 1,","-      env: { NODE_ENV: \"production\", PORT: \"3200\" },","-    },","-    {","-      name: \"kalshi-scheduler\",","-      script: \"dashboard/run_scheduler.sh\",","-      interpreter: \"bash\",","-      instances: 1,","-    },","-    {","-      name: \"kalshi-monitor\",","-      script: \"dashboard/monitor.js\",","-      instances: 1,","-    },","-  ],","-};","-```","+resource \"aws_cloudwatch_log_group\" \"dashboard\" {","+  name              = \"/tokenfly/trading/dashboard\"","+  retention_in_days = 14","+}"," ","-### Step 4: Provision infrastructure with Terraform (~10 min)","+# ── Cost Alert ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+resource \"aws_budgets_budget\" \"trading\" {","+  name         = \"tokenfly-trading-monthly\"","+  budget_type  = \"COST\"","+  limit_amount = \"60\"","+  limit_unit   = \"USD\"","+  time_unit    = \"MONTHLY\""," ","-Use the existing `infrastructure/` modules. Create a new `trading` environment or reuse `dev`:","+  notification {","+    comparison_operator        = \"GREATER_THAN\"","+    threshold                  = 80","+    threshold_type             = \"PERCENTAGE\"","+    notification_type          = \"ACTUAL\"","+    subscriber_email_addresses = [var.alert_email]","+  }","+}"," ","+# ── Variables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+variable \"kalshi_api_key\"        { sensitive = true }","+variable \"dashboard_api_key\"     { sensitive = true }","+variable \"trading_alert_webhook\" { default = \"\" }","+variable \"key_pair_name\"         { default = \"tokenfly-trading\" }","+variable \"alert_email\"           {}","+variable \"allowed_cidr\"          { description = \"Your IP in CIDR: 1.2.3.4/32\" }","+","+# ── Outputs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────","+output \"instance_ip\" { value = aws_eip.trading.public_ip }","+output \"ssh_command\"  { value = \"ssh -i ~/.ssh/${var.key_pair_name}.pem ec2-user@${aws_eip.trading.public_ip}\" }","+output \"dashboard_url\" { value = \"http://${aws_eip.trading.public_ip}:3199\" }","+```","+","+### 3. EC2 Bootstrap Script (`infrastructure/trading/user_data.sh`)","+"," ```bash","-cd infrastructure/environments/dev   # or create environments/trading/","+#!/bin/bash","+set -e"," ","-# terraform.tfvars (trading-specific)","-cat > terraform.tfvars <<EOF","-env                  = \"trading\"","-aws_region           = \"us-east-1\"","-vpc_cidr             = \"10.1.0.0/16\"","-availability_zones   = [\"us-east-1a\", \"us-east-1b\"]","-public_subnet_cidrs  = [\"10.1.0.0/24\", \"10.1.1.0/24\"]","-private_subnet_cidrs = [\"10.1.2.0/24\", \"10.1.3.0/24\"]","-nat_gateway_count    = 1","-task_cpu             = 256","-task_memory          = 512","-desired_count        = 1","-min_capacity         = 1","-max_capacity         = 1","-image_tag            = \"latest\"","+# Install Docker","+dnf install -y docker aws-cli","+systemctl enable --now docker","+usermod -aG docker ec2-user","+","+# Docker Compose plugin","+mkdir -p /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins","+curl -sL \"https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/latest/download/docker-compose-linux-x86_64\" \\","+  -o /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose","+chmod +x /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose","+","+# Fetch secrets from Secrets Manager","+SECRET=$(aws secretsmanager get-secret-value \\","+  --secret-id \"${secret_arn}\" \\","+  --region \"${aws_region}\" \\","+  --query SecretString --output text)","+","+# Parse secret JSON values","+KALSHI_API_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\"    | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['KALSHI_API_KEY'])\")","+API_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\"           | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['API_KEY'])\")","+DASHBOARD_API_KEY=$(echo \"$SECRET\" | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['DASHBOARD_API_KEY'])\")","+JWT_SECRET=$(echo \"$SECRET\"        | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['JWT_SECRET'])\")","+DB_PASSWORD=$(echo \"$SECRET\"       | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d['DB_PASSWORD'])\")","+WEBHOOK=$(echo \"$SECRET\"           | python3 -c \"import sys,json;d=json.load(sys.stdin);print(d.get('TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK',''))\")","+","+# Write env file (600 permissions — not world-readable)","+mkdir -p /opt/tokenfly","+cat > /opt/tokenfly/.env <<EOF","+NODE_ENV=production","+PAPER_TRADING=true","+","+KALSHI_API_KEY=$KALSHI_API_KEY","+API_KEY=$API_KEY","+DASHBOARD_API_KEY=$DASHBOARD_API_KEY","+JWT_SECRET=$JWT_SECRET","+","+DB_HOST=${db_host}","+DB_PORT=5432","+DB_NAME=${db_name}","+DB_USER=${db_user}","+DB_PASSWORD=$DB_PASSWORD","+PGSSLMODE=require","+","+MAX_POSITION_SIZE=50","+MAX_DAILY_LOSS=200","+MAX_DRAWDOWN=10","+MAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE=500","+MAX_CONCENTRATION=20","+","+TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK=$WEBHOOK"," EOF","+chmod 600 /opt/tokenfly/.env"," ","-terraform init","-terraform plan    # review — should create ~35 resources","-terraform apply","-```","+# Clone repo (replace with actual repo URL)","+cd /opt/tokenfly","+git clone https://github.com/tokenflyai/aicompany.git ."," ","-### Step 5: Deploy ECS task definition","+# Initialize DB schema","+export $(grep -v '^#' .env | xargs)","+cd agents/bob/backend","+node -e \"","+  const {Pool}=require('pg');","+  const fs=require('fs');","+  const pool=new Pool();","+  const sql=fs.readFileSync('db/schema.sql','utf8')","+    +fs.readFileSync('db/schema_strategies.sql','utf8')","+    +fs.readFileSync('db/schema_risk.sql','utf8');","+  pool.query(sql)","+    .then(()=>{console.log('DB init OK');process.exit(0)})","+    .catch(e=>{console.error(e);process.exit(1)});","+\"","+cd /opt/tokenfly"," ","-The `infrastructure/modules/ecs` module creates the ECS service. Override the container definition to point to the trading image and inject secrets:","+# Start stack","+docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build","+echo \"Tokenfly trading stack started\"","+```"," ","-Add to `infrastructure/modules/ecs/main.tf` (or create `infrastructure/modules/trading_task/`):","+### 4. Production Docker Compose (`docker-compose.prod.yml`)"," ","-```hcl","-# ECS Task Definition — Trading Pipeline","-resource \"aws_ecs_task_definition\" \"trading\" {","-  family                   = \"${var.name_prefix}-trading\"","-  requires_compatibilities = [\"FARGATE\"]","-  network_mode             = \"awsvpc\"","-  cpu                      = 256","-  memory                   = 512","-  execution_role_arn       = aws_iam_role.ecs_execution.arn","-  task_role_arn            = aws_iam_role.ecs_task.arn","+```yaml","+version: \"3.9\"","+services:","+  dashboard:","+    build:","+      context: .","+      dockerfile: Dockerfile","+    container_name: tokenfly-dashboard","+    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env","+    ports:","+      - \"3199:3199\"","+    volumes:","+      - ./agents:/app/agents","+      - ./public:/app/public","+      - /tmp/aicompany_runtime_logs:/tmp/aicompany_runtime_logs","+    restart: unless-stopped","+    logging:","+      driver: awslogs","+      options:","+        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/dashboard","+        awslogs-region: us-east-1","+        awslogs-stream: dashboard"," ","-  container_definitions = jsonencode([","-    {","-      name  = \"trading-pipeline\"","-      image = \"${var.ecr_repo_url}:${var.image_tag}\"","-      portMappings = [{ containerPort = 3200, hostPort = 3200 }]","-      ","-      secrets = [","-        {","-          name      = \"KALSHI_API_KEY\"","-          valueFrom = \"arn:aws:secretsmanager:${var.aws_region}:${var.aws_account_id}:secret:tokenfly/trading/kalshi-api-key\"","-        },","-        {","-          name      = \"DASHBOARD_API_KEY\"","-          valueFrom = \"arn:aws:secretsmanager:${var.aws_region}:${var.aws_account_id}:secret:tokenfly/trading/dashboard-api-key\"","-        }","-      ]","+  trading-api:","+    build:","+      context: ./agents/bob/backend","+      dockerfile: Dockerfile.api","+    container_name: tokenfly-trading-api","+    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env","+    ports:","+      - \"8080:8080\"","+    restart: unless-stopped","+    logging:","+      driver: awslogs","+      options:","+        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/pipeline","+        awslogs-region: us-east-1","+        awslogs-stream: trading-api"," ","-      environment = [","-        { name = \"NODE_ENV\",       value = \"production\" },","-        { name = \"PORT\",           value = \"3200\" },","-        { name = \"PAPER_TRADING\",  value = \"true\" },   # NEVER false without founder approval","-        { name = \"KALSHI_DEMO\",    value = \"true\" }","-      ]","+  scheduler:","+    build:","+      context: ./agents/bob/backend","+      dockerfile: Dockerfile.scheduler","+    container_name: tokenfly-scheduler","+    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env","+    restart: unless-stopped","+    logging:","+      driver: awslogs","+      options:","+        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/pipeline","+        awslogs-region: us-east-1","+        awslogs-stream: scheduler","+```"," ","-      mountPoints = [","-        {","-          sourceVolume  = \"trading-output\"","-          containerPath = \"/app/output\"","-          readOnly      = false","-        }","-      ]","+### 5. Dockerfiles for Trading Backend"," ","-      logConfiguration = {","-        logDriver = \"awslogs\"","-        options = {","-          awslogs-group         = \"/ecs/${var.name_prefix}-trading\"","-          awslogs-region        = var.aws_region","-          awslogs-stream-prefix = \"ecs\"","-        }","-      }","+**`agents/bob/backend/Dockerfile.api`**:","+```dockerfile","+FROM node:20-alpine","+WORKDIR /app","+COPY package.json package-lock.json ./","+RUN npm ci --omit=dev","+COPY . .","+EXPOSE 8080","+ENV PORT=8080","+CMD [\"node\", \"api/server.js\"]","+```"," ","-      healthCheck = {","-        command     = [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"node -e \\\"require('http').get('http://localhost:3200/api/health', r => process.exit(r.statusCode===200?0:1)).on('error',()=>process.exit(1))\\\"\"]","-        interval    = 30","-        timeout     = 5","-        retries     = 3","-        startPeriod = 15","-      }","-    }","-  ])","+**`agents/bob/backend/Dockerfile.scheduler`**:","+```dockerfile","+FROM node:20-alpine","+WORKDIR /app","+COPY package.json package-lock.json ./","+RUN npm ci --omit=dev","+COPY . .","+# Replaces run_scheduler.sh — same 10-minute loop, Docker handles restarts","+CMD [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done\"]","+```"," ","-  volume {","-    name = \"trading-output\"","-    efs_volume_configuration {","-      file_system_id     = var.efs_file_system_id","-      transit_encryption = \"ENABLED\"","-      authorization_config {","-        access_point_id = var.efs_access_point_id","-        iam             = \"ENABLED\"","-      }","-    }","-  }","-}","+### 6. Terraform Variables (`infrastructure/trading/terraform.tfvars`)","+","+```hcl","+# !! Add to .gitignore — never commit !!","+kalshi_api_key        = \"your-kalshi-api-key\"","+dashboard_api_key     = \"your-dashboard-api-key\"","+trading_alert_webhook = \"https://hooks.slack.com/services/...\"","+key_pair_name         = \"tokenfly-trading\"","+alert_email           = \"alerts@tokenfly.ai\"","+allowed_cidr          = \"YOUR_IP/32\""," ```"," ","-### Step 6: Verify deployment (~5 min)","+### 7. Deploy Commands (One-Time)"," "," ```bash","-# Check ECS service status","-aws ecs describe-services \\","-  --cluster tokenfly-trading \\","-  --services trading-pipeline \\","-  --query 'services[0].{status:status,running:runningCount,desired:desiredCount}'","+# 1. Create EC2 SSH key pair","+aws ec2 create-key-pair \\","+  --key-name tokenfly-trading \\","+  --query 'KeyMaterial' \\","+  --output text > ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem","+chmod 400 ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem"," ","-# Tail CloudWatch logs","-aws logs tail /ecs/tokenfly-trading-trading --follow","+# 2. Create Terraform state bucket","+aws s3api create-bucket \\","+  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\","+  --region us-east-1","+aws s3api put-bucket-versioning \\","+  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\","+  --versioning-configuration Status=Enabled"," ","-# Test dashboard API via ALB","-curl -H \"x-api-key: $DASHBOARD_API_KEY\" \\","-  https://<ALB_DNS>/api/health","+# 3. Deploy infrastructure","+cd infrastructure/trading","+terraform init","+terraform plan  -var-file=terraform.tfvars","+terraform apply -var-file=terraform.tfvars"," ","-# Confirm scheduler is running (look for 10-min cycle logs)","-aws logs filter-log-events \\","-  --log-group-name /ecs/tokenfly-trading-trading \\","-  --filter-pattern \"Pipeline OK\"","+# 4. Verify","+INSTANCE_IP=$(terraform output -raw instance_ip)","+curl -s http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health        # expect {\"ok\":true,...}","+ssh -i ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\","+  \"docker ps\"                                       # expect 3 containers"," ```"," "," ---"," ","-## Scheduler: run_scheduler.sh on AWS","+## Environment Variables Reference"," ","-The scheduler (`dashboard/run_scheduler.sh`) runs as a sidecar process inside the same ECS task via PM2. It loops every 600 seconds calling `live_runner.js`.","+| Variable | Source | Description |","+|----------|--------|-------------|","+| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Kalshi trading API credentials |","+| `API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Dashboard API auth token |","+| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Alias for API_KEY (internal calls) |","+| `JWT_SECRET` | Secrets Manager (auto-generated) | JWT signing key, 64-char random |","+| `DB_HOST` | Terraform output (auto) | RDS endpoint |","+| `DB_PORT` | user_data | `5432` |","+| `DB_NAME` | Terraform (auto) | `kalshi_trading` |","+| `DB_USER` | Terraform (auto) | `trading_user` |","+| `DB_PASSWORD` | Secrets Manager (auto-generated) | RDS password |","+| `PGSSLMODE` | user_data | `require` (RDS enforces TLS) |","+| `PAPER_TRADING` | user_data | `true` — **change to `false` requires Founder approval** |","+| `KALSHI_DEMO` | optional | `1` to use Kalshi demo API instead of live |","+| `MAX_POSITION_SIZE` | user_data | Max contracts per position (50) |","+| `MAX_DAILY_LOSS` | user_data | Daily loss ceiling USD (200) |","+| `MAX_DRAWDOWN` | user_data | Max drawdown % (10) |","+| `MAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE` | user_data | Max total exposure USD (500) |","+| `TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK` | Secrets Manager | Slack/webhook URL for trade alerts |","+| `NODE_ENV` | user_data | `production` |"," ","-**Alternative: EventBridge Scheduler** (cleaner, more observable)","+---"," ","-If the while-loop approach causes issues (e.g., task restarts lose state), migrate to EventBridge:","+## Scheduler Design"," ","-```bash","-# Create EventBridge rule — runs every 10 minutes","-aws scheduler create-schedule \\","-  --name kalshi-pipeline-run \\","-  --schedule-expression \"rate(10 minutes)\" \\","-  --target '{","-    \"Arn\": \"<ECS_CLUSTER_ARN>\",","-    \"RoleArn\": \"<SCHEDULER_ROLE_ARN>\",","-    \"EcsParameters\": {","-      \"TaskDefinitionArn\": \"<TASK_DEF_ARN>\",","-      \"LaunchType\": \"FARGATE\",","-      \"NetworkConfiguration\": { \"awsvpcConfiguration\": { \"Subnets\": [\"<SUBNET_ID>\"], \"AssignPublicIp\": \"DISABLED\" } }","-    }","-  }' \\","-  --flexible-time-window '{\"Mode\": \"OFF\"}'","+`run_scheduler.sh` runs `live_runner.js` every 10 minutes. The container replaces it:","+","+```dockerfile","+CMD [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done\"]"," ```"," ","-This runs `live_runner.js` as a short-lived task instead of a daemon — better for cost and observability.","+- `restart: unless-stopped` in Docker Compose handles crashes automatically","+- Logs stream to CloudWatch via `awslogs` driver","+- Future option: AWS EventBridge Scheduler → ECS Fargate task (zero idle cost, no EC2 needed)"," "," ---"," ","-## Monitoring Hooks","+## Monitoring"," ","-CloudWatch alarms are already wired in `infrastructure/main.tf` via the SNS module. For the trading pipeline specifically:","+### CloudWatch Metric Filter — Pipeline Failures"," ","-| Alarm | Metric | Threshold | SNS Topic |","-|-------|--------|-----------|-----------|","-| Pipeline stopped | ECS RunningTaskCount = 0 | 5 min | `p0_critical` |","-| High error rate | CW Logs filter: \"Pipeline FAILED\" | > 3 in 30 min | `p1_alert` |","-| Dashboard unhealthy | ALB HealthyHostCount < 1 | 5 min | `p1_alert` |","-| Memory pressure | ECS MemoryUtilization > 80% | 10 min | `infra_ops` |","+```bash","+aws logs put-metric-filter \\","+  --log-group-name /tokenfly/trading/pipeline \\","+  --filter-name PipelineFailures \\","+  --filter-pattern \"Pipeline FAILED\" \\","+  --metric-transformations \\","+    metricName=PipelineFailures,metricNamespace=Tokenfly,metricValue=1","+```"," ","-Subscribe your email to the SNS topics:","+### CloudWatch Alarm — Alert on Failure","+"," ```bash","-aws sns subscribe \\","-  --topic-arn <P0_CRITICAL_ARN> \\","-  --protocol email \\","-  --notification-endpoint your@email.com","+aws cloudwatch put-metric-alarm \\","+  --alarm-name tokenfly-pipeline-failure \\","+  --metric-name PipelineFailures \\","+  --namespace Tokenfly \\","+  --statistic Sum \\","+  --period 600 \\","+  --threshold 1 \\","+  --comparison-operator GreaterThanOrEqualToThreshold \\","+  --evaluation-periods 1 \\","+  --alarm-actions arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:ACCOUNT:tokenfly-alerts"," ```"," ","-The existing `monitor.js` (Liam's work) handles application-level alerts (stale data, PnL anomalies, failed trades) — those run inside the container and can POST to Slack or write to CloudWatch custom metrics.","+### Key metrics to watch","+| Metric | Threshold | Action |","+|--------|-----------|--------|","+| Pipeline FAILED in logs | Any occurrence | Page via SNS |","+| EC2 CPUUtilization | > 80% for 5 min | Investigate / upgrade instance |","+| RDS FreeStorageSpace | < 2 GB | Expand allocated storage |","+| Monthly spend | > $48 | Budget alert fires to email |"," "," ---"," ","-## Security Notes (coordinate with Heidi)","+## Monthly Cost Estimate"," ","-1. **Secrets**: API keys via Secrets Manager only — never in task definition plaintext or env files","-2. **Network**: ECS task runs in private subnets; ALB in public subnets. No direct internet access to container","-3. **IAM least privilege**: ECS task role has read-only Secrets Manager + EFS read-write only","-4. **PAPER_TRADING guard**: Default `true` in both Dockerfile and task definition — double protection against accidental live orders","-5. **Auth**: `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` required for all `/api/*` endpoints (existing `requireAuth` middleware in `dashboard_api.js`)","+| Resource | Spec | Cost/month |","+|----------|------|------------|","+| EC2 t3.small | 2 vCPU, 2 GB RAM | ~$15 |","+| RDS db.t3.micro | PostgreSQL 16, 20 GB | ~$17 |","+| EBS gp3 20 GB | EC2 root volume | ~$2 |","+| Elastic IP | Static IP | ~$4 |","+| CloudWatch Logs | ~5 GB/month | ~$3 |","+| Secrets Manager | 1 secret | ~$0.40 |","+| Data transfer | ~10 GB out | ~$1 |","+| **Total** | | **~$42/month** |"," ","+Cost alert fires at $48 (80% of $60 budget). Defined in Terraform.","+","+**GCP equivalent** (if preferred): `e2-small` (~$13) + Cloud SQL `db-f1-micro` (~$10) + Cloud Logging ≈ $30/month. Same architecture, swap `aws_` providers for `google_` — no application code changes.","+"," ---"," ","-## Quick-Start Checklist (Day 1)","+## Security Notes"," ","-- [ ] AWS account + CLI configured","-- [ ] ECR repo created","-- [ ] Secrets created in Secrets Manager (KALSHI_API_KEY, DASHBOARD_API_KEY)","-- [ ] `Dockerfile.trading` created at repo root","-- [ ] `ecosystem.trading.config.js` created in `agents/bob/backend/`","-- [ ] Docker image built and pushed to ECR","-- [ ] Terraform applied (VPC, ECS cluster, ALB, EFS, SNS)","-- [ ] ECS task definition created with secrets injection","-- [ ] ECS service deployed and running (1 task)","-- [ ] Health check passing (`/api/health` returns 200)","-- [ ] CloudWatch log group showing scheduler cycles","-- [ ] SNS email subscription confirmed for p0_critical alerts","-- [ ] `PAPER_TRADING=true` verified in running task env","+1. **Network isolation**: RDS is in private subnets — unreachable from internet. EC2 is the only database client.","+2. **Secrets at rest**: API keys fetched from Secrets Manager at boot, written to `/opt/tokenfly/.env` with `chmod 600`. Rotate by updating the Secrets Manager secret and re-running `user_data.sh` (or SSHing in and restarting containers).","+3. **SSH lockdown**: `allowed_cidr` variable restricts SSH and dashboard access to a single IP. Update after deploy if your IP changes.","+4. **Paper trading gate**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` by default. `live_runner.js` enforces: `const PAPER_TRADING = process.env.PAPER_TRADING !== 'false'`. Flipping to live requires explicit Founder approval (consensus.md entry #1).","+5. **IAM least-privilege**: EC2 role has only `secretsmanager:GetSecretValue` + CloudWatch write. No admin, no S3 read, no EC2 describe."," ","-Total time: **~4-6 hours** for a single operator with AWS CLI access.","+---","+","+## Rollback","+","+```bash","+# Stop containers only (preserves RDS data)","+ssh ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\","+  \"docker compose -f /opt/tokenfly/docker-compose.prod.yml down\"","+","+# Roll back to previous git commit + restart","+ssh ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \"cd /opt/tokenfly && git revert HEAD && \\","+  docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build\"","+","+# Destroy all infrastructure (RDS snapshot taken automatically)","+cd infrastructure/trading && terraform destroy -var-file=terraform.tfvars","+```","+","+---","+","+## Day-One Checklist","+","+- [ ] `aws configure` with IAM user (EC2, RDS, Secrets Manager, IAM, S3, Budgets permissions)","+- [ ] Create SSH key pair: `aws ec2 create-key-pair --key-name tokenfly-trading`","+- [ ] Fill in `terraform.tfvars` with real API keys (never commit this file)","+- [ ] `terraform init && terraform apply`","+- [ ] SSH in, verify `docker ps` shows 3 containers running","+- [ ] `curl http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health` returns `{\"ok\":true}`","+- [ ] Tail pipeline log: `docker logs -f tokenfly-scheduler`","+- [ ] Confirm `PAPER_TRADING=true` before any order execution","+- [ ] Set `allowed_cidr` to your real IP in tfvars + `terraform apply`","+","+---","+","+*Quinn — Cloud Engineer | Agent Planet*","+*All infrastructure is code. `infrastructure/trading/` is the source of truth — no manual console changes.*"]}],"originalFile":"# Cloud Deployment Plan — Kalshi Trading Pipeline\n**Author**: Quinn (Cloud Engineer)\n**Task**: T267\n**Date**: 2026-04-03\n**Target**: AWS (primary) with GCP notes where applicable\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDeploy the Kalshi trading pipeline as a containerized workload on AWS. The system consists of three processes:\n\n| Process | Source | Port | Description |\n|---------|--------|------|-------------|\n| `kalshi-dashboard` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js` | 3200 | Trade signals API |\n| `kalshi-scheduler` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard/run_scheduler.sh` | — | Runs `live_runner.js` every 10 min |\n| `kalshi-monitor` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard/monitor.js` | — | Alerts if pipeline stalls |\n\nA one-person operator can deploy this in a single day following the steps below.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nInternet\n    │\n    ▼\nRoute 53 (optional domain)\n    │\n    ▼\nALB (HTTPS :443 → HTTP :3200)\n    │\n    ▼\nECS Fargate Task (trading-pipeline)\n  ├── kalshi-dashboard    :3200\n  ├── kalshi-scheduler    (no port — cron loop)\n  └── kalshi-monitor      (no port — polling loop)\n    │\n    ▼\nAWS Secrets Manager\n  └── KALSHI_API_KEY, DASHBOARD_API_KEY\n```\n\nNo database required. Trade signals are written to JSON files; PnL state is file-based. EFS mounts the `agents/bob/output/` directory for persistence across task restarts.\n\n**Monthly cost estimate** (us-east-1, on-demand):\n| Resource | Config | $/month |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| ECS Fargate | 0.25 vCPU / 512 MB, 24×7 | ~$9 |\n| ALB | 1 instance | ~$18 |\n| EFS | < 1 GB | < $1 |\n| Secrets Manager | 2 secrets | $0.80 |\n| CloudWatch Logs | ~1 GB/mo | ~$0.50 |\n| **Total** | | **~$29/month** |\n\nTo cut cost to ~$11/month: drop the ALB and expose the dashboard directly (no HTTPS) — acceptable for a single-operator internal tool.\n\n---\n\n## Container Choice: AWS Fargate\n\n**Why Fargate over EC2:**\n- No instance management, patching, or AMI rotation\n- Scales to zero when stopped; billing is per-second\n- Sufficient for a single trading pipeline (scheduler runs every 10 min, CPU burst only)\n\n**Why not Lambda:**\n- The scheduler is a `while true; sleep 600` loop — Lambda's max execution time (15 min) doesn't fit\n- live_runner.js needs persistent file output between runs\n\n**Why not GCP Cloud Run:**\n- Existing Terraform modules are AWS-native (ECS, ALB, EFS, Secrets Manager)\n- Switch to GCP Cloud Run only if Kalshi API latency to GCP us-central1 is significantly better\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nInjected at runtime from **AWS Secrets Manager** — never hardcoded in container or task definition.\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Yes (live trading) | Kalshi REST API key — obtain from kalshi.com |\n| `KALSHI_DEMO` | No | `\"false\"` = live mode; default = demo/paper mode |\n| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | Yes (production) | Bearer token for `/api/*` auth on port 3200 |\n| `PAPER_TRADING` | No | Default `true` — set `\"false\"` only after founder approval |\n| `NODE_ENV` | Yes | `\"production\"` |\n| `PORT` | Yes | `3200` (dashboard API) |\n\n**Critical**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` is the default and must remain so until founder explicitly approves live order submission (per team consensus rule #1).\n\n### Secrets Manager setup (one-time)\n```bash\n# Create secrets\naws secretsmanager create-secret \\\n  --name \"tokenfly/trading/kalshi-api-key\" \\\n  --secret-string \"YOUR_KALSHI_API_KEY\"\n\naws secretsmanager create-secret \\\n  --name \"tokenfly/trading/dashboard-api-key\" \\\n  --secret-string \"$(openssl rand -hex 32)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Deployment Steps (Day 1)\n\n### Prerequisites\n- AWS account with CLI configured (`aws configure`)\n- Docker installed locally\n- Terraform >= 1.6\n- Node.js 20 (for local build/test)\n\n### Step 1: Build and push container image (~15 min)\n\n```bash\n# From aicompany/ root\ncd /path/to/aicompany\n\n# Create ECR repo (one-time)\naws ecr create-repository --repository-name tokenfly-trading --region us-east-1\n\n# Authenticate Docker to ECR\naws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 \\\n  | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin \\\n    <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com\n\n# Build trading pipeline image\ndocker build -f Dockerfile.trading -t tokenfly-trading:latest .\n\n# Tag and push\ndocker tag tokenfly-trading:latest \\\n  <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/tokenfly-trading:latest\ndocker push <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/tokenfly-trading:latest\n```\n\n### Step 2: Create Dockerfile.trading\n\nThe existing `Dockerfile` serves the agent dashboard. The trading pipeline needs its own image:\n\n```dockerfile\n# Dockerfile.trading\nFROM node:20-alpine\n\nRUN apk add --no-cache bash\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Install production deps\nCOPY agents/bob/backend/package.json agents/bob/backend/package-lock.json ./\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\n\n# Copy trading pipeline source\nCOPY agents/bob/backend/ ./\n\n# Create output directory for trade signals\nRUN mkdir -p /app/output\n\nEXPOSE 3200\n\nENV NODE_ENV=production \\\n    PORT=3200 \\\n    PAPER_TRADING=true\n\n# Start all three processes via PM2\nRUN npm install -g pm2\nCMD [\"pm2-runtime\", \"ecosystem.trading.config.js\"]\n```\n\n### Step 3: Create PM2 config for trading processes\n\n```javascript\n// ecosystem.trading.config.js\nmodule.exports = {\n  apps: [\n    {\n      name: \"kalshi-dashboard\",\n      script: \"dashboard_api.js\",\n      instances: 1,\n      env: { NODE_ENV: \"production\", PORT: \"3200\" },\n    },\n    {\n      name: \"kalshi-scheduler\",\n      script: \"dashboard/run_scheduler.sh\",\n      interpreter: \"bash\",\n      instances: 1,\n    },\n    {\n      name: \"kalshi-monitor\",\n      script: \"dashboard/monitor.js\",\n      instances: 1,\n    },\n  ],\n};\n```\n\n### Step 4: Provision infrastructure with Terraform (~10 min)\n\nUse the existing `infrastructure/` modules. Create a new `trading` environment or reuse `dev`:\n\n```bash\ncd infrastructure/environments/dev   # or create environments/trading/\n\n# terraform.tfvars (trading-specific)\ncat > terraform.tfvars <<EOF\nenv                  = \"trading\"\naws_region           = \"us-east-1\"\nvpc_cidr             = \"10.1.0.0/16\"\navailability_zones   = [\"us-east-1a\", \"us-east-1b\"]\npublic_subnet_cidrs  = [\"10.1.0.0/24\", \"10.1.1.0/24\"]\nprivate_subnet_cidrs = [\"10.1.2.0/24\", \"10.1.3.0/24\"]\nnat_gateway_count    = 1\ntask_cpu             = 256\ntask_memory          = 512\ndesired_count        = 1\nmin_capacity         = 1\nmax_capacity         = 1\nimage_tag            = \"latest\"\nEOF\n\nterraform init\nterraform plan    # review — should create ~35 resources\nterraform apply\n```\n\n### Step 5: Deploy ECS task definition\n\nThe `infrastructure/modules/ecs` module creates the ECS service. Override the container definition to point to the trading image and inject secrets:\n\nAdd to `infrastructure/modules/ecs/main.tf` (or create `infrastructure/modules/trading_task/`):\n\n```hcl\n# ECS Task Definition — Trading Pipeline\nresource \"aws_ecs_task_definition\" \"trading\" {\n  family                   = \"${var.name_prefix}-trading\"\n  requires_compatibilities = [\"FARGATE\"]\n  network_mode             = \"awsvpc\"\n  cpu                      = 256\n  memory                   = 512\n  execution_role_arn       = aws_iam_role.ecs_execution.arn\n  task_role_arn            = aws_iam_role.ecs_task.arn\n\n  container_definitions = jsonencode([\n    {\n      name  = \"trading-pipeline\"\n      image = \"${var.ecr_repo_url}:${var.image_tag}\"\n      portMappings = [{ containerPort = 3200, hostPort = 3200 }]\n      \n      secrets = [\n        {\n          name      = \"KALSHI_API_KEY\"\n          valueFrom = \"arn:aws:secretsmanager:${var.aws_region}:${var.aws_account_id}:secret:tokenfly/trading/kalshi-api-key\"\n        },\n        {\n          name      = \"DASHBOARD_API_KEY\"\n          valueFrom = \"arn:aws:secretsmanager:${var.aws_region}:${var.aws_account_id}:secret:tokenfly/trading/dashboard-api-key\"\n        }\n      ]\n\n      environment = [\n        { name = \"NODE_ENV\",       value = \"production\" },\n        { name = \"PORT\",           value = \"3200\" },\n        { name = \"PAPER_TRADING\",  value = \"true\" },   # NEVER false without founder approval\n        { name = \"KALSHI_DEMO\",    value = \"true\" }\n      ]\n\n      mountPoints = [\n        {\n          sourceVolume  = \"trading-output\"\n          containerPath = \"/app/output\"\n          readOnly      = false\n        }\n      ]\n\n      logConfiguration = {\n        logDriver = \"awslogs\"\n        options = {\n          awslogs-group         = \"/ecs/${var.name_prefix}-trading\"\n          awslogs-region        = var.aws_region\n          awslogs-stream-prefix = \"ecs\"\n        }\n      }\n\n      healthCheck = {\n        command     = [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"node -e \\\"require('http').get('http://localhost:3200/api/health', r => process.exit(r.statusCode===200?0:1)).on('error',()=>process.exit(1))\\\"\"]\n        interval    = 30\n        timeout     = 5\n        retries     = 3\n        startPeriod = 15\n      }\n    }\n  ])\n\n  volume {\n    name = \"trading-output\"\n    efs_volume_configuration {\n      file_system_id     = var.efs_file_system_id\n      transit_encryption = \"ENABLED\"\n      authorization_config {\n        access_point_id = var.efs_access_point_id\n        iam             = \"ENABLED\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Step 6: Verify deployment (~5 min)\n\n```bash\n# Check ECS service status\naws ecs describe-services \\\n  --cluster tokenfly-trading \\\n  --services trading-pipeline \\\n  --query 'services[0].{status:status,running:runningCount,desired:desiredCount}'\n\n# Tail CloudWatch logs\naws logs tail /ecs/tokenfly-trading-trading --follow\n\n# Test dashboard API via ALB\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: $DASHBOARD_API_KEY\" \\\n  https://<ALB_DNS>/api/health\n\n# Confirm scheduler is running (look for 10-min cycle logs)\naws logs filter-log-events \\\n  --log-group-name /ecs/tokenfly-trading-trading \\\n  --filter-pattern \"Pipeline OK\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Scheduler: run_scheduler.sh on AWS\n\nThe scheduler (`dashboard/run_scheduler.sh`) runs as a sidecar process inside the same ECS task via PM2. It loops every 600 seconds calling `live_runner.js`.\n\n**Alternative: EventBridge Scheduler** (cleaner, more observable)\n\nIf the while-loop approach causes issues (e.g., task restarts lose state), migrate to EventBridge:\n\n```bash\n# Create EventBridge rule — runs every 10 minutes\naws scheduler create-schedule \\\n  --name kalshi-pipeline-run \\\n  --schedule-expression \"rate(10 minutes)\" \\\n  --target '{\n    \"Arn\": \"<ECS_CLUSTER_ARN>\",\n    \"RoleArn\": \"<SCHEDULER_ROLE_ARN>\",\n    \"EcsParameters\": {\n      \"TaskDefinitionArn\": \"<TASK_DEF_ARN>\",\n      \"LaunchType\": \"FARGATE\",\n      \"NetworkConfiguration\": { \"awsvpcConfiguration\": { \"Subnets\": [\"<SUBNET_ID>\"], \"AssignPublicIp\": \"DISABLED\" } }\n    }\n  }' \\\n  --flexible-time-window '{\"Mode\": \"OFF\"}'\n```\n\nThis runs `live_runner.js` as a short-lived task instead of a daemon — better for cost and observability.\n\n---\n\n## Monitoring Hooks\n\nCloudWatch alarms are already wired in `infrastructure/main.tf` via the SNS module. For the trading pipeline specifically:\n\n| Alarm | Metric | Threshold | SNS Topic |\n|-------|--------|-----------|-----------|\n| Pipeline stopped | ECS RunningTaskCount = 0 | 5 min | `p0_critical` |\n| High error rate | CW Logs filter: \"Pipeline FAILED\" | > 3 in 30 min | `p1_alert` |\n| Dashboard unhealthy | ALB HealthyHostCount < 1 | 5 min | `p1_alert` |\n| Memory pressure | ECS MemoryUtilization > 80% | 10 min | `infra_ops` |\n\nSubscribe your email to the SNS topics:\n```bash\naws sns subscribe \\\n  --topic-arn <P0_CRITICAL_ARN> \\\n  --protocol email \\\n  --notification-endpoint your@email.com\n```\n\nThe existing `monitor.js` (Liam's work) handles application-level alerts (stale data, PnL anomalies, failed trades) — those run inside the container and can POST to Slack or write to CloudWatch custom metrics.\n\n---\n\n## Security Notes (coordinate with Heidi)\n\n1. **Secrets**: API keys via Secrets Manager only — never in task definition plaintext or env files\n2. **Network**: ECS task runs in private subnets; ALB in public subnets. No direct internet access to container\n3. **IAM least privilege**: ECS task role has read-only Secrets Manager + EFS read-write only\n4. **PAPER_TRADING guard**: Default `true` in both Dockerfile and task definition — double protection against accidental live orders\n5. **Auth**: `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` required for all `/api/*` endpoints (existing `requireAuth` middleware in `dashboard_api.js`)\n\n---\n\n## Quick-Start Checklist (Day 1)\n\n- [ ] AWS account + CLI configured\n- [ ] ECR repo created\n- [ ] Secrets created in Secrets Manager (KALSHI_API_KEY, DASHBOARD_API_KEY)\n- [ ] `Dockerfile.trading` created at repo root\n- [ ] `ecosystem.trading.config.js` created in `agents/bob/backend/`\n- [ ] Docker image built and pushed to ECR\n- [ ] Terraform applied (VPC, ECS cluster, ALB, EFS, SNS)\n- [ ] ECS task definition created with secrets injection\n- [ ] ECS service deployed and running (1 task)\n- [ ] Health check passing (`/api/health` returns 200)\n- [ ] CloudWatch log group showing scheduler cycles\n- [ ] SNS email subscription confirmed for p0_critical alerts\n- [ ] `PAPER_TRADING=true` verified in running task env\n\nTotal time: **~4-6 hours** for a single operator with AWS CLI access.\n"}}
